{"insight":"The old hunger can wear holy clothes","publicTitle":"When Letting Go Becomes Control","plainSummary":"The urge to find what remains after release can be the old need for control in a spiritual form.","atAGlance":"After letting go, some people still demand a clear result. That demand can come from old habits, not from the path itself. A person who lives by control may bring control into spiritual practice. The test is whether the pressure follows the person or the method.","keyPoints":["Release is not another project to master.","The search for peace can become another form of strain.","Compare people and methods before blaming the path."],"match":["pressure after letting go"],"tags":["letting go","control","practice","self"]}
